\begin_layout Standard
Note on errors.
 Consider the case where all probabilities are zero and window size is less
 than the length of the chain.
 This case corresponds to windowed surface areas, where the surface area
 of a residue is calculated considering only local residues, which can be
 calculated exactly by repeated surface area calculation for isolated sequence
 segments.
 The above calculation will not give exact results and errors will be both
 positive and negative.
 Positive errors (surface area calculation too large) result from intersections
 that are occluded in the full alpha complex and the occluding atom is not
 local.
 Negative errors result from occluded facets due to not correcting for overlaps.
\end_layout

